<HEADLINE> Solar Power Markets to Continue Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 6 (Xinhua) -- World solar markets are growing at
ten times the rate of the oil industry, U.S. Worldwatch Institute
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Solar power has grown at 16 percent annually since 1990
compared to merely 1.4 percent for oil energy growth, the
Washington-based institute said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 alone, sales of solar cells expanded over 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Solar power capacity has reached 800 megawatts, representing
only less than one percent of global power supplies.
</P>
<P>
As governments move to implement the Kyoto Protocol on climate
change and replace fossil fuels, solar power is poised to
benefit.
</P>
<P>
The institute said for the 2 billion people worldwide who are
not yet connected to power lines, solar energy is often the most
affordable way to get electricity. 
</P>
